name: Louise Haigh
summary: Keir Starmer has criticized Louise Haigh's call to boycott P&O Ferries, leading to backlash from union leaders who view this as an "unacceptable" attack. The Telegraph suggests that Starmer is scapegoating Haigh to preserve a £1 billion investment deal with P&O's owner, DP World. Despite Starmer's criticism, P&O's owner will still attend an investment summit in the UK. In a positive development, the government has intervened to prevent a repeat of the P&O Ferries scandal, strengthening workers' rights at sea. Louise Haigh is a Transport Secretary who has been involved in discussions about the HS2 high-speed rail line's extension to London Euston. However, Downing Street's handling of the port giant's investment has caused chaos, with the company withdrawing a £1 billion announcement after Haigh's criticism of P&O's actions.

name: Baba Siddique
summary: On Thursday, former Maharashtra Minister and NCP leader Baba Siddique was shot dead near his son's office in Mumbai, India. Two accused have been apprehended. The police are investigating a potential connection to the Lawrence Bishnoi gang. Siddique, a key figure in Ajit Pawar's NCP faction, played a pivotal role in reconciling Salman Khan and Shah Rukh Khan after their altercation at Katrina Kaif's birthday party. The incident has sparked widespread shock and mourning. Among those who visited Lilavati Hospital to pay their respects were Shilpa Shetty, Raj Kundra, Sanjay Dutt, and others.
